(24, '\n				Anwar Rasheed\n			', '', '', 1, 'Anwar Rasheed is a Malayali Indian film director notable for his debut film Rajamanikyam (2005) starring Mammootty. His second feature film was Chotta Mumbai (2007), which had Mohanlal in the lead role. He reunited with Mammootty for his third feature Annan Thambi (2008).', 0),
(25, '\n				Joshiy\n			', '', '', 1, 'Joshiy is an Indian film director popular for his comparability big budget action movies in Malayalam cinema with a huge local star cast. He made his debut with Tiger Salim (1978). He is popular for such films as New Delhi (1987), Lelam (1997), Runway (2004), Naran (2005), and Twenty:20 (2008).', 0),
(26, 'Vinayan', '', '', 1, 'Vinayan is an Indian film director, mainly of Malayalam movies. He started his career with the film Super Star, in which he used a Mohanlal look-alike in the lead role.[1]', 0),
(27, 'Rajasenan', '586768863e7d84fe756be7814a8ce8f2.jpg', '', 1, 'Rajasenan (Malayalam: à´°à´¾à´œà´¸àµ‡à´¨à´¨àµâ€) is an Indian film director, screenwriter, and occasional actor who has worked in Malayalam cinema.[1] His notable films include Ayalathe Adheham (1992), Meleparambil Aanveedu (1993), CID Unnikrishnan B.A., B.Ed. (1994) and Aadyathe Kanmani (1995).[2]', 0),
(28, 'Shajoon Kariyal', '', '', 1, 'Shajoon Kariyal is an Indian film director working in Malayalam cinema. Shajoon was born in 1966 in Kozhikode, Kerala and had his primary education from Govt. Ganapath High School, Chalappuram. He started his film career in 1984, at the age of 18, as an assistant director to I. V. Sasi.[1] He worked as the assistant or associate director to many films including Uyarangalil (1984), Anubandham (1985), Karimpin Poovinakkare (1985), Aavanazhi (1986), 1921 (1988), Douthyam (1989), Varthamana Kalam (1990), Arhatha (1990), Midhya (1991), Neelagiri (1991) and Varnapakittu (1997).[2] He debuted as a di', 0),
(29, 'A. K. Lohithadas', 'cfb2c34dad82acec64333a7216b68dcd.jpg', '', 1, 'Ambazhathil Karunakaran Lohithadas (à´…à´®àµà´ªà´´à´¤àµà´¤à´¿à´²àµâ€ à´•à´°àµà´£à´¾à´•à´°à´¨àµâ€ à´²àµ‹à´¹à´¿à´¤à´¦à´¾à´¸àµ May 10, 1955 - June 28, 2009) was an Indian screenwriter, director, and producer known for his extensive work in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(30, 'Lenin Rajendran', '', '', 1, 'Lenin Rajendran is an Indian film director and screenwriter who has worked in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(31, 'Rajiv Anchal', '', '', 1, 'Rajiv Anchal is a screenwriter and film director from Kerala. He has directed eight feature films. Of late, he has based his movies in the United States. He is the life member of International Film And Television Club of Asian Academy Of Film &amp; Television. His magnum opus is a Malayalam film, Guru, which is a symbolic and allegorical movie about the blind faith which has been perpetuated on the human mankind. Guru was officially the Indian submission for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film in 1997. His Beyond the Soul won three awards at the New York International Independent ', 0),
(32, 'Thulasidas', '', '', 1, 'Thulasidas is an Indian director of Malayalam movies. Since the late 1980s he has directed some 25 movies.', 0),
(33, 'Priyadarshan', 'ec1c73ca355401473ca6cc2767bef4f6.jpg', '', 1, 'Priyadarshan Nair is an Indian film director, producer, and screenwriter. In a career spanning over two decades, Priyadarshan has directed over 80 films in several Indian languages including Malayalam, Hindi, Tamil, and Telugu. Though he began his career in Malayalam cinema in 1984, Priyadarshan has been mainly active in Hindi cinema for the past decade.', 0),
(34, 'Kamal (director)', '0af3b79332bae86051162992f6859d97.png', '', 1, 'Kamaluddin Mohammed, usually credited as Kamal, is a Malayali Indian film director. His first film was Mizhineer Pookkal in 1986 and to date, he has directed more than 32 movies, among which include 2 non-malayalam movies, one each in Tamil and Hindi. Apart from his role as a director, Kamal was recently elected as the general secretary of MACTA (Malayalam Cine Technicians Association). He is also the executive member of the Kerala Chalachitra Academy.', 0),
(35, 'Sathyan Anthikad', '', '', 1, 'Sathyan Anthikad is an Indian film director and screenwriter known primarily for his family based Malayalam films.', 0),
(36, 'K. Madhu			', '', '', 1, 'K. Madhu is a Malayalam film director.Popular for his suspense and investigation thrillers, K.Madhu has a long list of hits in his kitty.', 0),
(37, '\n				Shafi (director)\n			', '', '', 1, 'Shafi is an Indian film director who mainly works in Malayalam cinema, known for his comedy films. He has also directed a Tamil film. The director Rafi of the Rafi Mecartin duo is his elder brother. His well known films include Kalyanaraman (2002), Thommanum Makkalum (2005), Mayavi (2007), Chocolate (2007), Chattambinadu (2009), and Marykkundoru Kunjaadu (2010).', 0),
(38, 'Joshiy', '8c178985ad47ab838265695613da7f1d.png', '', 1, 'Joshiy is an Indian film director popular for his comparability big budget action movies in Malayalam cinema with a huge local star cast. He made his debut with Tiger Salim (1978). He is popular for such films as New Delhi (1987), No.20 Madras Mail (1990), Dhruvam (1993), Nair Saab (1989), Sainyam (1994), Lelam (1997), Runway (2004), Naran (2005), and Twenty:20 (2008).', 0),
(39, '\n				Kamal (director)\n			', '', '', 1, 'Kamaluddin Mohammed, usually credited as Kamal, is a Malayali Indian film director. His first film was Mizhineer Pookkal in 1986 and to date, he has directed more than 32 movies, among which include 2 non-malayalam movies, one each in Tamil and Hindi. Apart from his role as a director, Kamal was recently elected as the general secretary of MACTA (Malayalam Cine Technicians Association). He is also the executive member of the Kerala Chalachitra Academy.', 0),
