(43, 'Mohanlal', '9f472b48e6b6b0c6f0f94e362d98d864.jpg', '43bb73b6e7009aa53ed89c05ffd9997168.jpg', 1, 'Mohanlal Vishwanathan Nair (born 21&#160;May 1960),[3] known mononymously as Mohanlal, is an Indian actor and producer best known for his work in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(44, 'Suresh Gopi', 'e51600686c6576d32f0b2d3ad5578729.jpg', '', 1, 'Suresh Gopinathan Nair (born 26 June 1959),[1] often credited as Suresh Gopi (Malayalam: à´¸àµà´°àµ‡à´·àµ à´—àµ‹à´ªà´¿), is a national award winning Indian film actor who works mainly in Malayalam cinema; he is famous for his roles in police dramas. He is noted for his leading roles as much as his character roles. He is also famous for his philanthropic efforts.[4]', 0),
(45, 'Mammootty', 'b88241112c81d57dd1865cc20b4ca8e7.jpg', '45195e274d1dc852562d92f107fe974eff.jpeg', 1, 'Mammootty (born Muhammadkutty Ismail Panaparambil on 7 September 1951[1][3]) is an Indian film actor and producer who works mainly in Malayalam cinema. He has also acted in a few Tamil, Hindi, Telugu, and Kannada films. During a career spanning more than three decades, he has acted in more than 360 films,[4] and is only next to Prem Nazir in the number of lead roles in Indian films. He also appeared in the highest number of dual roles (nine) in Malayalam films.[5]', 0),
(46, 'Kanika', '', '', 1, 'Divya Venkatasubramaniam (Tamil: à®¤à®¿à®µà¯à®¯à®¾ à®µà¯†à®™à¯à®•à®Ÿà®šà¯à®ªà¯à®°à®®à®£à®¿à®¯à®®à¯; born 3 July 1982), best known by her stage name Kanika (also spelled Kaniha),[1][2] is an Indian film actress, occasional dubbing artist, playback singer, and TV anchor. Making her debut in the 2002 Tamil film Five Star, she went on to work in other South Indian film industries, including Telugu, Malayalam and Kannada, as well. She is perhaps best known for her performances as Eashwari in her debut film Five Star, Gayathri in Varalaru - History of Godfather and Thenmozhi in Autograph. She m', 0),
(47, 'Nedumudi Venu', 'b7dc5ee5db25a55dc5dcaf5ddec7c9e0.jpg', '', 1, 'K. Venu Gopal (born 22 May 1948), known popularly by his stage name Nedumudi Venu (Malayalam: à´¨àµ†à´Ÿàµà´®àµà´Ÿà´¿ à´µàµ‡à´£àµ), is a Malayalam film actor from Kerala, India. He has also written screenplays and has directed one film.[1][2][3][4]', 0),
(48, 'Biju Menon', 'f36704a39d206cd785b424a98c1d3e3f.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Biju Menon is an Indian film actor who has mainly worked in Malayalam cinema, along with a couple of Tamil and Telugu films. He appears mostly in supporting roles, but has also acted in antagonistic roles. He made his debut in 1995 in Puthran.', 0),
(49, 'Saikumar (Malayalam actor)', 'd9ace906dba7716b53b5762373bc0ba3.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Saikumar is a popular Malayalam actor. He is known for his handling of serious roles, though he started his career with comedy roles. Of late, he has been doing many negative roles as well.', 0),
(50, 'Dileep (actor)', 'f38509b67e2d88f499643dae4571b934.jpg', '', 1, 'Dileep (Malayalam: à´¦à´¿à´²àµ€à´ªàµ; born Gopalakrishnan Padmanabhan Pillai on 27 October 1968) is an Indian film actor, mimicry artist and producer best known for his work in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(51, 'Jagathy Sreekumar', '5d15159ebd20739f445e58caf1e6a126.jpg', '', 1, 'Sreekumar Achary, better known by his stage name Jagathy Sreekumar, is an Indian film actor who has performed in more than 1,000 Malayalam films.[1] He has also directed two films and has written screenplays for two films. His stage name is derived from the neighbourhood of Jagathy in Thiruvananthapuram, from where he hails.', 0),
(52, 'Vijayaraghavan (actor)', '6223fe21ab9eef6a308be78ab8a52af0.jpg', '', 1, 'Vijayaraghavan (Malayalam: à´µà´¿à´œà´¯à´°à´¾à´˜à´µàµ») is an Indian actor who mainly acts in Malayalam cinema. He is popular for his character roles. He is the son of popular drama and cinema artist N. N. Pillai.', 0),
(53, 'Samyuktha Varma', '', '', 1, 'Samyuktha Varma ( à´¸à´‚à´¯àµà´•àµà´¤ à´µàµ¼à´®àµà´® ), born November 26, 1982[1] is an award winning actress in Malayalam Movie Industry. She entered filmdom through the Malayalam movie Veendum Chila Veettukaryangal directed by Sathyan Anthikkad. Then she acted in several Malayalam feature films and bagged some awards. Later she left the scene after her marriage to actor Biju Menon.[2]', 0),
(54, 'Revathi', '2372ef6940cc58fcfa4feba21ac0824a.jpg', '', 1, 'Revathy (born as Asha Kelunni Kutty on 8 July 1966) is an Indian actress and film director. She has acted in Tamil, Malayalam, Kannada, Telugu and Hindi films, directed several feature-length films, and has acted in and produced multiple television programs, totaling over twenty years of experience in the entertainment industry and over a hundred films to her credit. She has won several accolades, including three National Film Awards, in three different categories, and six Filmfare Awards South.', 0),
(55, 'Vasundhara Das', '', '', 1, 'Vasundhara Das (born 1977), is an Indian singer and actress. She has acted in Hindi, Tamil, Kannada and Malayalam films. She is the co-founder of world music band Arya. As a playback singer, she is best remembered for singing "Shakalaka Baby" from the Tamil film Mudhalvan, which was also her debut song. She has performed many hit songs in Hindi and Tamil films thereafter.', 0),
(56, 'Devayani (actress)', '', '', 1, 'Devayani (born Sushma Jayadev on 22 June 1973) is an Indian film actress. She starred in numerous Tamil, Telugu and Malayalam films, along with a few Hindi films and one Bengali film. She received the Tamil Nadu State Film Awards for her performances in the films Kadhal Kottai and Surya Vamsam.[1][2] She has also appeared in the films Bharathi, Friends and Azhagi as well as in the Sun TV series Kolangal.', 0),
(57, 'Mukesh (actor)', '59101849fc40f7a3737b598d054a3547.jpg', '', 1, 'Mukesh (born Mukesh Babu on October 21, 1960) is an Indian film actor and producer known for his work in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(58, 'Kalabhavan Mani', 'c8347d5b295f2745c53e889c5a90ad84.JPG', '', 1, 'Kalabhavan Mani (Malayalam: à´•à´²à´¾à´­à´µàµ» à´®à´£à´¿; born 1 January 1971) is a South Indian actor and singer. He began his career in Malayalam film industry, later he became a busy artist in Tamil and telugu industry, especially in villain roles. Although he began his career as a comedian, he proved his versatility in various roles such as serious actor, heroic and villain. He has acted in a number of films in Malayalam and Tamil. He has proved his acting talent in the movies called Vasantiyum Lakshmiyum Pinne Njanum, in which he plays a blind street singer.', 0),
(59, 'Rahman (actor)', 'e82126e2e26d58d5341dea30cf2105ed.JPG', '', 1, 'Rahman (born Rashin Rahman on 23 May 1967 in Abu Dhabi, Trucial States) is an Indian film actor who has acted in Malayalam, Tamil, and Telugu films. He made his debut in Koodevide (1983), and has appeared in more than 150 films, including Parannu Parannu Parannu (1984), Chilambu (1986), Pappan Priyappetta Pappan (1986), Pudhu Pudhu Arthangal (1989), and Nee Pathi Naan Pathi (1991).', 0),
(60, 'Anwar Rasheed', 'ab32ee0df8f759ddf1d44d9a2f5a02a8.png', '', 1, 'Anwar Rasheed is a Malayali Indian film director notable for his debut film Rajamanikyam (2005) starring Mammootty. His second feature film was Chotta Mumbai (2007), which had Mohanlal in the lead role. He reunited with Mammootty for his third feature Annan Thambi (2008).', 0),
(61, 'Prithviraj Sukumaran', '1f7a2c890745179b32d3d2e306ae65ed.jpg', '', 1, 'Prithviraj Sukumaran (born 16 October 1982[1] in Thiruvananthapuram, Kerala) credited mononymously as Prithviraj, is an Indian film actor and producer best known for his work in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(62, 'Narain (actor)', 'd958eec78bf0cf6da24b616010ea62e5.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Narain (born as Sunil Kumar) is an Indian film actor, who appears in Malayalam and Tamil films.', 0),
(63, 'Jayasurya', '1873c835a5ffacc4da909c9b4cdf2747.jpg', '', 1, 'Jayasurya (Malayalam à´œà´¯à´¸àµà´°àµà´¯; born in Thrippunithura, Kochi, India) is an Indian film actor and comedian.', 0),
(64, 'Thilakan', 'f27ca18df6353aa71cf8e0885aa25634.JPG', '', 1, 'Surendranatha Thilakan (Malayalam: à´¸àµà´°àµ‡à´¨àµà´¦àµà´°à´¨à´¾à´¥ à´¤à´¿à´²à´•à´¨àµâ€; born 10 December 1938), known mononymously as Thilakan, is an Indian actor who works in Malayalam cinema and theatre. Thilakan is regarded as one of the finest actors in Indian cinema[1][2], known for his excellence in character roles. He was awarded Padma Shri on 25 January 2009.[3]', 0),
(65, 'Balachandra Menon', '', '', 1, 'Balachandra Menon is an Indian film actor, director, script writer, lyricist, and producer who works in Malayalam cinema. He made some popular films in the 1980s and 1990s. He won the National Film Award for Best Actor for his role as Ismail in the 1998 film Samantharangal, which was also directed by him.', 0),
(66, 'Geetha (actress)', '', '', 1, 'Geetha (Telugu: à°—à±€à°¤à°¾;Kannada: à²—à³€à²¤à²¾;Tamil: à®•à¯€à®¤à®¾) is an Indian actress who has performed in Telugu, Malayalam, Tamil, Kannada and Hindi films. She debuted in the Tamil language film Bhairavi as Rajnikantâ€™s sister. Since then she has acted in films of all the South Indian languages, and in a few Hindi films.[1][2]', 0),
(67, 'Jomol', '', '', 1, 'Gowri Chandrasekhara Pillai (born Jomol) is an Indian actress who appeared in Malayalam films. She has had major roles in films like Niram, Piriyadha Varam Vendum and Deepasthambham Mahascharyam. She was born in Koodathayi near Thiruvambady in Calicut district. A Christian by birth, she later changed her name to Gowri Chandrasekhara Pillai after her marriage with Chandrasekhara Pillai, who is from Mumbai. She adopted Hinduism.', 0),
(68, 'Samvrutha Sunil', 'bf072a85222d3e2ec6a241fc804332ef.jpg', '', 1, 'Samvrutha Sunil (also known as Samvritha; born October 31, 1986) is a South Indian actress from Kerala, predominantly appearing in Malayalam films. She was introduced to the film industry through the Malayalam film Rasikan directed by Lal Jose. She has appeared in Telugu and Tamil films as well. Samvrutha was born in Kannur district in the state of Kerala.She is also supposed to be an ideal actress in the selection of costumes', 0),
(69, 'Ananya (actress)', '944fe1941546f0c1bdae873a03929b88.jpg', '', 1, 'Ayilya Nair (born 29 March 1987), better known by her stage name Ananya, is an Indian film actress, who appears in Malayalam and Tamil films. She made her acting debut in Malayalam with Positive (2008) and debuted the following year in Tamil with Naadodigal, which emerged a critical and commercial success. She currently has a list of films in her hands in Malayalam and Tamil.', 0),
(70, 'Manikuttan', '1d3090acf144dcef061e22f261aa63d4.png', '', 1, 'Thomas James, better known by his stage name, Manikuttan, is an Indian film and television actor.', 0),
(71, 'Suraj Venjaramoodu', '49659096854fe61c90ff2ad27c1073f7.png', '', 1, 'Suraj Venjaramood is a Malayalam film actor and mimicry artist.[1] He mainly plays comic roles, though he has played some lead roles as well.[2]', 0),
(72, 'Saji Surendran', '', '', 1, 'Saji Surendan is an Indian film director in Malayalam films.', 0),
(73, 'Mamta Mohandas', 'd76dd79abfeb9483b7e346e0ceb36be6.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Mamta Mohandas (Malayalam:à´®à´‚à´®àµà´¤ à´®àµ‹à´¹à´¨àµâ€à´¦à´¾à´¸àµâ€Œ), is an Indian film actress and playback singer. She has mainly acted in Malayalam films, besides few Telugu and Tamil productions and one Kannada film. She has won two Filmfare Awards, for Best Female Playback Singer in Telugu in 2007 and for Best Actress in Malalayam in 2010.', 0),
(74, 'Vineeth Sreenivasan', 'bb6041723f83d7d780bce76562d377b9.jpg', '', 1, 'Vineeth Sreenivasan is an Indian playback singer, film actor, director, and screenwriter. He is the son of actor Sreenivasan. He made his debut as a director with his film Malarvaadi Arts Club (2010).', 0),
