(91, 'T. K. Rajeev Kumar', '9e3bf7d1e9c94a0de774dadc1afeea41.jpg', '', 1, 'TK RAJEEV KUMAR (born September 20, 1961 in Kottayam, India) is an National Award winning Director of Malayalam films.He is settled in Trivandrum, Kerala. Rajeev Kumar served as the Chairman of Kerala State Chalachitra Academy from 2003 to 2006. He was also the Director for the International Film Festival of Kerala from 2003 to 2006 and was the Vice Chairman of Kerala State Chalachitra Academy in 2002.[1] He was nominated as Jury Chairman for Kerala State Film Awards 2007.', 0),
(92, 'Mohan (actor)', '', '', 1, 'Mohan (born 23 August 1956 as Mohan Rao) is a popular Kollywood actor. He hails from the Udupi district of Karnataka. He derived his name Kokila Mohan after debuting in a film called Kokila, which starred Kamal Haasan in the lead role.[1][2] He considers Balu Mahendra as his mentor.[3] He has acted in Kannada films, Telugu films and Malayalam films, but his main contribution was to Tamil cinema where he has acted in over 80 films.', 0),
(93, 'Padmini Kolhapure', 'e677e2474fc8eaf945f652a9af0da70a.jpg', '', 1, 'Padmini Kolhapure (born 1 November 1965) is an Indian actress who appeared in Bollywood films during the 1970s and 1980s.', 0),
(94, 'Saiju Kurup', '16f2efeae2c96cba34ab7b0df7275da7.jpg', '', 1, 'Saiju Kurup (also known as Anirudh in Tamil cinema) is an Indian actor in Malayalam cinema. His debut movie was the critically acclaimed movie Mayookham by Hariharan. He has starred in several films as the main lead, villain, supporting artiste and done guest appearances in several more.', 0),
(95, 'Sugeeth', '8a4c5e82788c39f9b2f9b98a36178bb3.png', '', 1, 'Sugeeth is a film director who made his debut through the Malayalam language movie Ordinary.[1]', 0),
(96, 'M. Sasikumar', 'b3f51714c7cad18836e9d0edf5df4d95.png', '', 1, 'M. Sasikumar is a Tamil film director, actor and producer. He is best known in the Tamil film industry for his debut film Subramaniapuram (2008). The low-budget film received attention for its original script, direction, screenplay, editing and accurate sets and costumes resurrecting Madurai from the 1980s.[1]', 0),
(97, 'Sreenivasan (actor)', '986e59eb8e5b4947f5b482b3350c595a.png', '', 1, 'Sreenivasan (Malayalam:à´¶àµà´°àµ€à´¨à´¿à´µà´¾à´¸à´¨àµâ€, born 6 April 1956) is an Indian film actor, screenwriter, director, and producer.[1] He is noted for his satirical, screwball, and black comedy screenplays in Malayalam cinema. As an actor he is famous for his comic performances.', 0),
(98, 'Pasupathy', 'a0ddd9b07da7e994a028228884c35319.png', '', 1, 'Pasupathy (Tamil: à®ªà®šà¯à®ªà®¤à®¿; born 18 May 1969) is an Indian film actor. He appeared in critically acclaimed roles in many noted films in Tamil cinema, essaying supporting, antagonistic, comedic as well as protagonistic roles. His performance in E (2006) earned him a Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor and a Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Supporting Actor. He also won an ITFA Best Supporting Actor Award for his role in Kuselan (2008). He has also appeared in Malayalam, Telugu, and Kannada films.', 0),
