(131, '\n				Penmatsa Subbaraju\n			', '', '', 1, 'Penmatsa Subbaraju is an actor and fighter in Tollywood. He acted in many hit Tollywood films like Amma Nanna O Tamil Ammayi,Arya and Pokiri. He is currently trying to turn as a character artist from his fighter image.', 0),
(132, 'Sukumar', 'a81c83ad9fec0ec6ada4f5b47e4ce7cc.png', '', 1, 'Sukumar Bandreddi (Telugu: à°¸à±à°•à±à°®à°¾à°°à± à°¬à±¦à°¡à±à°°à±†à°¡à±à°¡à°¿), better known by his first name, is a Tollywood film director and screenwriter. He worked as script associate and assistant director for the films Manasichi Choodu, Kshemanga Velli Labhanga Randi, Hanuman Junction and Dil, and made his directorial debut with Arya.', 0),
(133, 'Salim Kumar', 'b18350e91c6ddf93d10219d0c63e1333.jpg', '', 1, 'Salim Kumar (Malayalam: à´¸à´²à´¿à´‚ à´•àµà´®à´¾à´°àµâ€; born on 10 June 1968) is a National Award-winning Indian film actor and mimic predominantly acting in Malayalam cinema.', 0),
(134, 'Katrina Kaif', '', '', 1, 'Katrina Kaif (born 16 July 1984[2]) is a British Indian actress and former model who appears in Indian films, mainly in the Hindi-language film industry.[3][4] She has also appeared in Telugu and Malayalam films. She was voted the sexiest Asian woman in the world by Eastern Eye in the years 2008, 2009 and 2010.[5][6] Being a British citizen, she works in India on an employment visa.[1]', 0),
(135, 'I. V. Sasi', '', '', 1, 'Irruppam Veedu Sasidaran (Malayalam: à´‡à´°àµà´ªàµà´ªà´‚ à´µàµ€à´Ÿàµ à´¶à´¶à´¿à´§à´°àµ»), better known as I. V. Sasi, is a Malayali Indian film director who is known for his films of the 1970s, 80s and early 90s.', 0),
(136, 'Nikita Thukral', '57cdab59b69562f2abbb38fc61118d4f.jpg', '', 1, 'Nikita Thukral (born July 6, 1981) is an Indian film actress and model, who has acted in Telugu, Tamil, Kannada and Malayalam films. She is best known for her item number "Kodana Kodi" in Saroja.', 0),
(137, 'Jomon (director)', '03520c6f4e32f7afe9f7da7749a6d02a.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Jomon is an Indian screenwriter and director who is actively involved in Malayalam cinema. After working as assistant director in films like Aalkkoottathil Thaniye, Uyarangalil, Adiyozhukkukal, 1921 and Douthyam, Jomon became independent director with the Mammootty starrer Samrajyam, which established new technical dimensions in Malayalam cinema. The film established Jomon as an happening director of Malayalam cinema. However he failed to give consistent hit films.', 0),
(138, 'Ashish Vidyarthi', '5af3e45b507550639015d7fc90b9f2b6.jpg', '', 1, 'Ashish Vidyarthi (born 19 June 1962) is an Indian actor who worked predominantly in Hindi films and lately in South Indian films. He has won the National Film Award for Best Supporting Actor for film Drohkaal in 1995.', 0),
(139, 'Meena (actress)', '', '', 1, 'Meena Durairaj, (mononymously known as Meena, born in Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India) is a South Indian film and television actress. Meena debuted as a child artist in Telugu and Tamil films and has later starred in films produced by various regional industries. She is one of the most established actresses in the southern Indian film industry. In addition to acting, Meena is also a top model, singer, dancer, TV host and occasional dubbing artiste. At one time she was considered as the biggest south Indian actress by acting opposite Superstars of south India.', 0),
(140, 'Gopika', '5fb3f6c93038cf253d5f3513e5345dfa.jpg', '', 1, 'Gopika (born August 24, 1984[1][2] as Girly Anto) is an Indian film actress, who has predominantly starred in Malayalam films. Starting her career as a model, she ventured into acting with the film Pranayamanithooval (2003). She went on to appear in over 30 films, working in Tamil, Telugu and Kannada film industries as well.', 0),
(141, 'Prakash Raj', '', '', 1, 'Prakash Rai (born 26 March 1965), better known by his stage name Prakash Raj, is a National Award winning film actor, director and producer who has worked in Kannada, Telugu, Tamil, Hindi and Malayalam films.He got introduced to films by K. Balachander in the movie Duet (1994). In remembrance, he named his production company "Duet Movies".[2][3]', 0),
(142, 'Major Ravi', '', '', 1, 'Major A.K. Ravindran,[1] better known by his screen name Major Ravi is a former Indian Army Officer and a Malayali Indian filmmaker.', 0),
