(170, 'Thambi Ramaiah', '', '', 1, 'Thambi Ramaiah is an Indian film actor and director, who works in the Tamil film industry. He directed the Vadivelu-starrer Indiralohathil Na Azhagappan[1]; his performance in Mynaa, won a National Film Award for Best Supporting Actor.[2] Ramaiah has also been working occasionally as a lyricist.[3]', 0),
(171, 'Arjun Sarja', '', '', 1, 'Arjun Sarja (born Sreenivasa Sarja Ashok Babu Sakthi Prasad Arjun on 15 August 1964) is an Indian film actor and director.[3] Son of Kannada film star Shakti Prasad, he has primarily acted in Tamil films, and also appeared in Kannada, Malayalam and Telugu films.[4] The title "Action King" has been given to Arjun by fans, for the numerous action roles he has portrayed. He is also a black belt holder in karate.[5][1][6][7][8][9] He has done many movies in Tamil, Kannada, Malayalam and Telugu .[1]', 0),
