(198, 'Thiruvambadi Thamban', '', '', 1, 'Thiruvambadi Thamban  is a 2012 Malayalam film starring Jayaram and Haripriya in lead roles, directed by Padmakumar and written by S. Suresh Babu. It also marks the debut of Tamil actors Thambi Ramaiah and Kishore in Malayalam.[2] It also has Kalabhavan Mani, Nedumudi Venu, Suraj Venjaramoodu and Jagathy Sreekumar in supporting roles.This Movie is made on Indian rupee 12 crore.', 0),
(199, 'A. K. Sajan', '853ffe8a261768114002b6c4132a088e.png?303-4', '', 1, 'A. K. Sajan is a Malayalam screenwriter and director who is best known for his directorial debut Stop Violence (2002). He is the brother of A. K. Santhosh who wrote the script for the film. The movie had debutant Prithviraj Sukumaran and Chandra Lakshman in the lead roles. Asuravithu is a 2011 malayalam film written and directed by him after the movie Stop Violence, starring Azif Ali', 0),
