(209, 'Kadhalil Sodhappuvadhu Yeppadi', '', '', 1, 'Kadhalil Sodhappuvadhu Yeppadi (titled Love Failure in Telugu)  is a 2012 Indian bilingual romantic comedy film based on the same-titled short film directed by debutant Balaji Mohan and resembles to the English film (500) Days of summer. Starring Siddharth and Amala Paul,[2] the film was simultaneously produced in both Tamil and Telugu languages.[3] It was released worldwide on 17 February 2012 to high critical acclaim and was declar', 0),
(210, 'Nafisa Ali', '3173899a62a62be6e2ae138a62c4d521.png', '', 1, 'Nafisa Ali (born 18 January 1957) is an actress and social activist from India.', 0),
(211, 'Amal Neerad', 'f05bdc7172420cd39538aedebdea5d4f.jpg', '', 1, 'Amal Neerad (born on October 7, 1975 in Kottayam, Kerala, India) is an Indian film director, cinematographer, and screenwriter. Began his career as a cinematographer, he also turned into direction with Big B (2007).[1] He is known for his stylishly choreographed and photographed action scenes, often compared to Hollywood. He is famous and infamous among critics for his frequent use of stylized slow motion in action scenes.', 0),
(212, 'Rajan P. Dev', 'c3e6c7bcfa204428b6f439368ddf5039.jpg', '', 1, 'Rajan P Dev (29 May 1951 â€“ 29 July 2009) was an Indian film and stage actor. He was born in Cherthala in the Alappuzha district of the former state Thiru-Kochi (present day Kerala). He had acted in over 140 films in Malayalam, Tamil, Telugu and Kannada language films. He was noted for his villain roles laced with a touch of humour. He came into limelight for his characterisation of Kochuvava in the play Kattukuthira.[1] Rajan P. Dev died in Kochi Wednesday 29 July 2009 due to a liver disease.', 0),
