(218, 'Gajala', '28694a543f15536084025eee654d7057.png', '', 1, 'Gajala is an Indian film actress, who has appeared in Tamil, Malayalam and Telugu films. She has worked with actors like Dileep, Arjun Sarja and Jr. NTR.', 0),
(219, 'Madhu Warrier', '474faa0fe076add6e6fe74b8810c0659.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Madhu Warrier is a Malayalam actor who has played supporting roles in many malayalam movies.', 0),
(220, 'A. Karunakaran', '19816a19f5a4f448bfd6037b4d6eff84.png', '', 1, 'Before entering Telugu Film Industry, his parents forced him to join polytechnics.[citation needed] After finishing polytechnics in 1989, he went to Chennai. Instead, he became Cinema assistant director to other eminent directors such as Kathir, Shankar and started loving cinema as his career.Karunakaran''s first directorial film in 1998 was Tholi Prema starring Pawan Kalyan. Vasu followed, and then subsequent films Yuvakudu, Balu ABCDEFG, Happy, Darling, and recently, Endhukante Premanta. He made a cameo appearance in the movie Tholi Prema.', 0),
(221, 'K. P. A. C. Lalitha', '11094c58f1cfb45a6f7c3f90dc607d71.png', '', 1, 'Maheshwari Amma (born 25 February 1950) is better known by her stage name K.P.A.C. Lalitha. She is a National Award winning Indian film and stage actress. She was the wife of late filmmaker Bharathan.', 0),
(222, 'Fahadh Faasil', '', '', 1, 'Fahadh Faasil is an Indian film actor known for his work in Malayalam cinema. He made his debut in Kaiyethum Doorath (2001) directed by his father Fazil. After a sabbatical of nearly eight years, Fahadh had a resurrection of his career in the portmanteau film Kerala Cafe (2009). He earned critical acclaim for his performances in Chaappa Kurish (2011), Akam (2011), 22 Female Kottayam (2012) and Diamond Necklace (2012).', 0),
(223, 'Ustad Hotel', '4c16e4c72bdb74bb8b775f6d30c2b83d.jpg', '', 1, 'written by Anjali Menon and directed by Anwar Rasheed. It stars Dulquer Salmaan, Nithya Menon and Thilakan in the lead roles while Siddique, Mamukkoya and Lena play prominent supporting roles.[1][2][3] The film is about the strong bond between Karim, a Sufi Muslim, and his grandson Faizi.', 1),
(225, 'Usha Uthup', '6e3148499365c9bb454bedc01a1eaa82.jpg', '', 1, 'Usha Uthup (born November 8, 1947) is a popular Indian pop, jazz and playback singer. She is well known for popular hits in the late 1960s, 1970s and 1980s.[2][3]', 0),
(224, 'Fahad Fazil', '179ff8fc16d1118ec300fa20911680cf.jpg', '', 1, 'Fahad Fazil is an Indian film actor known for his work in Malayalam cinema. He made his debut in Kaiyethum Doorath (2002) directed by his father Fazil. After a sabbatical of nearly eight years, Fahadh had a resurrection of his career in the anthology film Kerala Cafe (2009). He earned critical acclaim for his performances in Chaappa Kurish (2011), Akam (2011), 22 Female Kottayam (2012) and Diamond Necklace (2012).', 0),
(226, 'Bharath Gopi', '76fc830dc58e3954bfcfa84cacc86978.jpg', '', 1, 'National Film Awards\n1995: Best Book on Cinema -\nAbhinayam Anubhavam\n(Acting and the Experience)\n1992: Best Film on Social Issues -\nYamanam\n1978: Best Actor - Kodiyettam', 0),
(227, 'Murali (Malayalam actor)', '32a6d58daebc493872c79fd60fca94bc.jpg', '', 1, 'Murali (Malayalam: à´®àµà´°à´³à´¿, 25 May 1954 - 6 August 2009) was an Indian actor and author. He was closely associated with the Communist Party of India (Marxist). He mainly acted in Malayalam and Tamil films. He won the National Award for Best Actor for his portrayal of a communist freedom fighter and professional weaver in the film Neythukaran (2002). He was also a stage actor and television actor. He was known for his powerful portrayal of character roles, lead roles, and negative roles. His last film was Aadhavan.', 0),
(228, 'Malayalam films of 2006', '5df9c25deaffff72c92bb14da8a056bd.png', '', 1, 'The following is a list of Malayalam films released in the year 2006.', 0),
(229, 'Cinema Company', '32c4d138757331cb2b241c1b705483f8.png', '', 1, 'Cinema Company is a 2012 Malayalam romantic comedy drama film written and directed by Mamas and starring mainly newcomers. Basil, Sanjeev, Shruthi and Badri play the roles of four intimate friends who dream to make a film.', 0),
(230, 'Akshay Kumar', 'd35a794388b8cdbbac71852102eb9675.jpg', '', 1, 'Akshay Kumar (born Rajiv Hari Om Bhatia)[1] on September 9, 1967[1]) is an Indian film actor, producer and martial artist who has appeared in over a hundred Hindi films. He has been nominated for Filmfare Award several times and won two times. When he began his acting career in the 1990s, he primarily starred in action films and was particularly known for his appearances in feature films commonly called the "Khiladi series", which included Khiladi (1992), Main Khiladi Tu Anari (1994), Sabse Bada Khiladi (1995), Khiladiyon Ka Khiladi (1996), Mr. and Mrs. Khiladi (1997), International Khiladi (1', 0),
(231, 'Jacqueline Fernandez', '688e239ee1a4dc285d2eaf5017429386.jpg', '', 1, 'Jacqueline Fernandez (born 11 August 1985) is a Sri Lankan actress[5] and model who appears in Bollywood films. Fernandez is a former model and beauty queen who won Miss Sri Lanka Universe in 2006. She has received an International Indian Film Academy Award and Stardust Award for Best Female Debut in 2010,[6] for her role in Aladin.', 0),
(232, 'John Abraham (actor)', '563c76a0ab39111110541d38707842b8.png', '', 1, 'John Abraham (born December 17, 1972) is an Indian film actor and film producer. After modeling for numerous advertisements and companies, Abraham made his film debut with Jism (2003), which earned him a Filmfare Best Debut Award nomination.[1] This was followed by his first commercial success, Dhoom (2004). He received two Filmfare Award nominations, for his negative roles in Dhoom, and then in Zinda (2006). He later appeared in the major critical success Water (2005).[2] He was nominated for a Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor for the film Baabul (2006). In 2012, he produced his first', 0),
(233, 'Sajid Khan (director)', 'b72c5e8479a10036b1a7332ead035fab.png', '', 1, 'Sajid Khan (Hindi: à¤¸à¤¾à¤œà¤¿à¤¦ à¤–à¤¾à¤¨; born Sajid Kamran Khan on November 23, 1971 in Mumbai, Maharashtra, India) is an Indian film-maker, actor, film director, script writer, talk show host and presenter and the younger brother of Bollywood choreographer and director Farah Khan.', 0),
(234, 'Abhishek Bachchan', 'bb0ab0fe698107c768e44f67eb5a1687.jpg', '', 1, 'Abhishek Bachchan (born 5 February 1976 in Mumbai, Maharashtra) is an Indian actor and producer. He is the son of Indian actors Amitabh Bachchan and Jaya Bachchan and is married to actress and former Miss World Aishwarya Rai.', 0),
(235, 'Rohit Shetty', '0ef9a5d2c06b0b1e44c371caaad8c209.jpg', '', 1, 'Rohit Shetty (born 14 March 1973) is an Indian film director, cinematographer and occasional actor. His work as director include the hits Golmaal, Golmaal Returns, All The Best: Fun Begins, Golmaal 3, Singham and Bol Bachchan.', 0),
(236, 'Sonam Kapoor', '2c5b3dff4c9dd6a55d70525d5f8240d7.jpg', '', 1, 'Sonam Kapoor (born 9 June 1985[1]) is an Indian film actress and fashion icon who appears in Bollywood films. Born to Indian film actor, Anil Kapoor, Kapoor chose acting as her career and followed the footsteps of her father.', 0),
(237, 'Bipasha Basu', 'a9c7aeee4cee2aa82a4d85898545e2a6.jpg', '', 1, 'Bipasha Basu (born 7 January 1979)[1] is an Indian actress who appears in Hindi language films. She has also worked in Telugu, Bengali and Tamil language films. She had a successful modeling career before venturing into films.[2]', 0),
(238, 'Abbas-Mustan', '725e1f1c679f43ead7a3b325c916121b.png', '', 1, 'Abbas and Mustan Burmawalla are a Hindi Bollywood director duo. They are known for directing films in the thriller and action genres. They have frequently cast Akshay Kumar, Bobby Deol and Akshaye Khanna in their films. Since Khiladi, the brothers have cast Johnny Lever in every single one of their movies except Aitraaz Naqaab and Taarzan: The Wonder Car. The duo direct landmark Bollywood films like Khiladi, Baazigar, Soldier, Ajnabee, Baadshah, Aitraaz, Humraaz, 36 China Town and Race.', 0),
(239, 'Naseeruddin Shah', '1867a0753381181d0b63ea242e3ca08e.png', '', 1, 'Naseeruddin Shah (born 20 July 1950) is an Indian/Bollywood film actor and director. He is widely considered to be one of the finest Indian stage and film actors. He is an influential actor of the Indian Parallel (New Wave) Cinema. Shah has won numerous awards in his career, including three National Film Awards, three Filmfare Awards for Best Actor, and a Best Actor Award (The Volpi Cup) at the Venice Film Festival. The Government of India has honored him with both the Padma Shri and the Padma Bhushan civilian awards for his contributions to Indian cinema.', 0),
(240, 'Kay Kay Menon', 'a01853e53f335fdba393a4cb5c9f8236.jpg', '', 1, 'Kay Kay Menon is an Indian actor.', 0),
(241, 'Atul Kulkarni', 'e4dce86f54eda1a21799689c433cad85.jpg', '', 1, 'Atul Kulkarni (born 10 September 1965) is an Indian actor who has won two National Awards and has attained the superstar status in Marathi film industry after successful movies like Valu and Natarang.', 0),
(242, 'Shiney Ahuja', 'ef97a5c17110ed4bce3f8ec8fb239c88.jpg', '', 1, 'Shiney Ahuja (born 15 May 1974) is an Indian actor who won the Filmfare Best Debut Award for Hazaaron Khwaishein Aisi in 2006.[1]', 0),
(243, 'Sayali Bhagat', '6deff32466ff6358ef85c521f0aad64e.png', '', 1, 'Sayali Bhagat (Gujarati&#160;; born 1 January 1984) is an Indian actress and former beauty queen. She competed in Femina Miss India 2004 and won the title of Femina Miss India World.[1]', 0),
