(249, 'Kareena Kapoor', '69e1d3d88268527aab937c538d0e5bbb.png', '', 1, 'Kareena Kapoor (pronounced [kÉ™ËˆriËnaË kÉ™ËˆpuËr]; born on 21 September 1980), often informally referred to as Bebo, is an Indian actress who appears in Bollywood films. During her career, Kapoor has been noted for her performances in a range of film genres; these include her work from contemporary romantic dramas to comedies, period films to major Bollywood productions, as well as less publicised independent films.[1][2]', 0),
(250, 'Boman Irani', '3398f25dc72cab463b0c955e7dd95e39.jpg', '', 1, 'Boman Irani (Hindustani pronunciation:&#160;[boËmaËn iËraËnËiË] Gujarati: àª¬à«‹àª®àª¨ àª‡àª°àª¾àª¨à«€; born 2 December 1959) is an Indian film and theatre actor and photographer. Irani is sometimes referred to as David Walliams of India.', 0),
(251, 'Shakun Batra', 'cfb9787ed00b6449795eb6038d9ae2f8.png', '', 1, 'Shakun batra is an Indian filmmaker. He had worked in many noted Bollywood movies as a assistant director, but he marked his Bollywood debut in early 2012; by directing the Ek Main Aur Ekk Tu[1][2].', 0),
(252, 'Payal Rohatgi', '5fcbf96fabb9f61896930fff6f91a9e5.png', '', 1, 'Payal Rohatgi (born in Hyderabad)[2] is an Indian actress and model who appears in Bollywood films.', 0),
(253, 'Prateik Babbar', 'a51956a80b7a588917bedb0036896e04.jpg', '', 1, 'Prateik Babbar (Hindi: à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¤à¥€à¤•, Marathi: à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¤à¥€à¤•) (born 28 November 1986) is an Indian actor. He is the son of late actress Smita Patil and actor turned politician Raj Babbar.', 0),
(254, 'Amy Jackson', '14a3116ba681ef598683e423d1c473b2.jpg', '', 1, 'Amy Louise Jackson (born 31 January 1991) is a British beauty pageant titleholder, model[2] and actress. She won the Miss Teen World competition in 2008, went on to win Miss Liverpool in 2009, and was hotly tipped to be Miss England in 2010 but lost out to Jessica Linley in the final.[3] She made her acting debut with the successful 2010 Tamil period-drama Madrasapattinam, which won her plaudits for her role and launched her acting career. She made her Bollywood debut with Ekk Deewana Tha (2012),[4] starring along side Prateik Babbar.\n', 0),
(255, 'Manu Rishi', '5791e89dfd0192eb58b4e330c981a69f.png', '', 1, 'Manu Rishi (Hindi: à¤®à¤¨à¥ à¤‹à¤·à¤¿) is an Indian film actor, lyricist, script and dialogue writer. Manu Rishi trained under theatre director Arvind Gaur for six years.[citation needed] He won the Filmfare Best Dialogue Award, 2009 for Oye Lucky! Lucky Oye![1] He also won the IIFA Best Dialogue award for Oye Lucky! Lucky Oye!', 0),
(256, 'Gautham Menon', '7bbea931452f0e6588dc916891b22488.jpg', '', 1, 'Gautham Vasudev Menon (born 25 February 1973) is an Indian film director and producer, who predominantly works in Tamil cinema. He has also directed a few films in Hindi and Telugu languages which are remakes of his own Tamil films. Many of his films have been critically acclaimed, most notably his semi-autobiographical Vaaranam Aayiram (2008), romantic classic Vinnaithaandi Varuvaayaa (2010), his action-thrillers Kaakha Kaakha (2003) and Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu (2006). Vaaranam Aayiram won the National Film Award for Best Feature Film in Tamil.', 0),
(257, 'Jackie Shroff', 'f42f655e201e451f83cd57724e8f5391.jpg', '', 1, 'Jackie Shroff (Hindi: à¤œà¥ˆà¤•à¥€ à¤¶à¥à¤°à¥‰à¤«à¤¼) (born 1 February 1957)[1] is an Indian actor. He has been in the Gujarati cinema and Hindi cinema (Bollywood) industries for almost 3 decades and has appeared in over 150 films in Hindi, Tamil, Telugu, Malayalam, Bengali, Kannada, and Marathi.', 0),
(258, 'Archana Joglekar', 'aaf0031d0a8ddf953cc53118731c697c.png', '', 1, 'Archana Joglekar is an Indian actress and classical dancer who has appeared in numerous Marathi and Hindi films and television serials. She is a renowned Kathak dancer and choreographer. She has learned Kathak from her mother Smt. Asha Joglekar, who is also a noted Kathak danseuse and instructor. In 1963, her mother founded a dance school in Mumbai called Archana Nrityalaya. In 1999, Archana opened a branch of this dance school in New Jersey, US.[1]', 0),
(259, 'Omi Vaidya', '4fc5f14b3f7eff594d69b67aa252c633.JPG', '', 1, 'Omi Vaidya (Marathi: à¤“à¤®à¥€ à¤µà¥ˆà¤¦à¥à¤¯) is an Indian American actor who is best known for his performance as Chatur Ramalingam or "The Silencer" in the 2009 Bollywood film, 3 Idiots.[2] In addition, Vaidya has directed two short films and worked as an editor on others. He has also appeared in a number of television programs and commercials.[3]', 0),
(260, 'Ali Zafar', '3b4d5d21403875734e8c64f98d9bb462.jpg', '', 1, 'Ali Zafar (Punjabi, Urdu: Ø¹Ù„ÛŒ Ø¸ÙØ±, born May 18, 1980 in Lahore, Pakistan) is a Pakistani musician, composer, song writer, singer, actor, painter and model,[1] popular for his music, acting in Pakistani dramas and now movies. His popular songs include his hits like "Channo", "Rangeen", "Chal Dil Merey", "Dekha", "Masty", "Jhoom", "Sajania", "Madhubala","Voh Dekhney Mein", "Dastan-e-ishq" and "Yar Dhadhi Ishq". He started his singing career with the song "Jugnuon Se Bhar Le Aanchal" in the film Shararat, directed by Pakistani actress and director Samina Peerzada but made a big mark with hi', 0),
(261, 'Vipin Sharma', '2ffe5dc17f23ac9766c55f5d2dc31dd5.png', '', 1, 'Vipin Sharma is an Indian actor born in New Delhi. He is a graduate of National School of Drama, New Delhi, India and the Canadian Film Centre, Toronto, Canada.[1] His first major role was as Nandakishore Avasti in Taare Zameen Par (Like Stars on Earth). For his role, he was nominated for a 2009 Star Screen Award for Best Supporting Actor.Post Taare Zameen Par Vipin has become an established actor in Bollywood. His work in Yeh Saali Zindagi,Ghajini and Saheb, Biwi Aur Gangster broke his stereotypical image of a stern father from TZP and has established him as a new entrant in Bollywood to watc', 0),
(262, 'Tigmanshu Dhulia', '2acb4f3403680061ea3d2d5c60e21864.png', '', 1, 'Tigmanshu Dhulia (born 3 July 1967) is an Indian film director, actor, screenwriter, and casting director. Dil Se.., for which he wrote the screenplay, was the first Hindi movie to chart in the UK top ten.[1]', 0),
(263, 'Shreyas Talpade', 'cf88bcb26b887d57c70c5e8e6191d4a7.png', '', 1, 'Shreyas Talpade (&#160;pronunciation&#160;(helpÂ·info); born 27 January 1976) is an Indian actor who appears in Marathi and Bollywood films.', 0),
(264, 'Rajeev Khandelwal', '239a694c796a76518fa7d1818936ba04.png', '', 1, 'Vijaya Laxmi', 0),
(265, 'Tusshar Kapoor', 'd4b28fb7bc67e4865eb1a25f22c4e1ac.png', '26593372f597784c35c11a52347a8adc738.jpeg', 1, 'Tusshar Kapoor (à¤¤à¥à¤·à¤¾à¤° à¤•à¤ªà¥‚à¤°; in Mumbai, Maharashtra) is an Indian actor. He is the son of Bollywood actor Jeetendra and Shobha Kapoor and sister of Ekta Kapoor. He studied at the University of Michigan and graduated with a BBA from the Stephen M. Ross School of Business.', 0),
(266, 'Kulraj Randhawa', '5f8765d73d1986aefdd9d30adb415922.jpg', '', 1, 'Kulraj Kaur Randhawa (born on 16 May 1983) is an Indian actress who shot to fame after her role as the bubbly â€œKareenaâ€ in the popular TV series Kareena Kareena.', 0),
(267, 'Samir Karnik', '8e668928e39ab78affbe2d58dd740816.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Samir Karnik (Punjabi: à¨¸à¨®à©€à¨° à¨•à¨¾à¨°à©à¨¨à¨¿à¨•, Hindi: à¤¸à¤®à¥€à¤° à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤•, Urdu: Ø³Ù…ÛŒØ± Ú©Ø§Ø±Ù†Ú©), is an Indian film director, producer and screenwriter of Hindi movies.', 0),
(268, 'Vidya Balan', '4a0437d70b9c36c8e992ab1f784aa804.jpg', '', 1, 'Vidya Balan (pronounced [Ê‹ÉªdÌªjaË baËlÉ™n]; born 1 January 1978)[1] is an Indian actress, who appears mainly in Hindi films, in addition to Bengali and Malayalam films. After graduating with a degree in sociology, she started her career starring in music videos, television shows and commercials, before making her feature film debut with the independent Bengali drama Bhalo Theko (2003). Balan received positive notice for her first Hindi film, Parineeta (2005), and followed it with a leading role in the blockbuster Lage Raho Munna Bhai (2006), and other such hit films as Guru, Heyy Babyy and', 0),
(269, 'Parambrata Chatterjee', '1d3c7b50e10b4efb096aaf5682d9f199.jpg', '', 1, 'Parambrata Chatterjee (pÃ´rombroto chÃ´ttopaddhae) is a Bengali Indian male actor and director of television and films,[1] who came to limelight after starring in the film Kahaani; starring along with Vidya Balan. His performance was greatly appreciated in the film.[2]', 0),
(270, 'Indraneil Sengupta', 'ccaa67cb2e456889417cfd19d1ccf3b2.png', '', 1, 'Indraneil Sengupta is an Indian model and actor, born in Assam and schooled and raised in Ahmedabad, India. He was a finalist in the 1999 Gladrags Manhunt Contest. In 2000, he moved to Mumbai to pursue modelling and modelled for designers like Rohit Bal and worked for choreographers like Marc Robinson and Achala Sachdev. He did commercials for the Tata Indigo Marina car, VIP Frenchie and Aquafina.', 0),
(271, 'Sujoy Ghosh', 'e48d1f3275c01332bc2145d19672e78b.png', '', 1, 'Sujoy Ghosh (born 1966) is a Bollywood film director.[1] He has directed Jhankaar Beats (2003), Home Delivery: Aapko... Ghar Tak (2005), Aladin (2009) and Kahaani (2012).[2][3]', 0),
(272, 'Mithun Chakraborty', 'a9990ebeb8cbc419b65e88efd10df2bb.png', '', 1, 'Mithun Chakraborty Miá¹­hun ChÃ´kroborti, born as Gouranga Chakraborty on June 16, 1950) is an Indian film actor, social activist, and entrepreneur, who has won three National Film Awards. He made his acting debut with the arthouse drama Mrigayaa (1976), for which he won his first National Film Award for Best Actor.', 0),
(273, 'Dalip Tahil', 'fa089482dcbd26ceb9cf42aaa10b5875.JPG', '', 1, 'Dalip Tahil (born 30 October 1952, Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India) is an Indian film, television and theatre actor. He did his schooling from the elite Sherwood College in Nainital, India and later graduated from Aligarh Muslim University, Aligarh.', 0),
(274, 'Goldy', 'bec929f0afe1e4231b50254def1687d9.png', '', 1, 'Goldy may refer to:', 0),
(275, 'Ashu Trikha', '54dd3c5843c1748653bc82f56991046d.png', '', 1, 'Ashu Trikha is an Indian film director and producer of Bollywood. He started his career with Arjun Rampal movie Deewaanapan which was produced by Vashu Bhagnani and then after a gap of 8 years he returned with Mithun Chakraborty movie Zindagi Tere Naam which also saw the return of Ranjeeta Kaur to Bollywood. But for unknown reasons, the movie is still unreleased. His second venture Baabarr had Mithun and Om Puri in lead roles. The film was critically accalimed and done moderate business at the box-office. Now he is doing his third film Enemmy with an ensemble cast of Mithun Chakraborty, Sunil ', 0),
(276, 'Saif Ali Khan', '65d39ef442326568312e3fe37fba8064.jpg', '', 1, 'Saif Ali Khan (pronounced&#160;[ËˆsÉ›Ëf É™Ëˆli ËˆxaËn]; born 16 August 1970) is an Indian actor known for his work in Bollywood films. He is the son of the cricket player and last titular Nawab of Pataudi, late Mansoor Ali Khan Pataudi, and actress Sharmila Tagore, a great-grandniece of poet Rabindranath Tagore.[1]', 0),
(277, 'Agent Vinod (2012&#32;film)', '03206defa4b18f5f4b47889132cbdbb4.jpg', '', 1, 'Agent Vinod a 2012 Indian action spy film directed by Sriram Raghavan. The movie borrows its name from the 1977 film of the same name. The film stars Saif Ali Khan and Kareena Kapoor in leading roles and also features Ravi Kishan, Prem Chopra, Ram Kapoor, Gulshan Grover, Maryam Zakaria and debutante Anshuman Ajai Singh. It was filmed in India, Morocco, Russia, Latvia, UK, South Africa and Pakistan. Agent Vinod was co-produced by Illuminati Films and Eros Entertainment[4]', 0),
(278, 'Staying Alive (2012&#32;film)', 'bf29a5da962bd2a3809aa0cd07ce34db.jpg', '', 1, 'Staying Alive is a 2012 Hindi-language social film directed by Anant Mahadevan, featuring Anant Mahadevan, Saurabh Shukla, Chandan Roy Sanyal in the lead roles. The films music was composed by Sanjay Chowdhury. The film was released on February 3rd, 2012.', 0);
