(279, 'Gramam', '6f08700523570090eb4ac2bce9910e74.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Gramam (Namma Gramam) is an Indian bilingual film written, directed and produced by yesteryear actor-producer Mohan Sharma. It was simultaneously made in Malayalam and Tamil languages under the titles Gramam and Namma Gramam respectively. It stars Nishan, Samvrutha, Nedumudi Venu, Sukumari, Mohan, Y. G. Mahendraa, Nalini and Fathima Babu. The film, which was well received by critics upon its screening at various film festivals, won two National Film Awards and two Kerala State Film Awards among other laurels.[1]', 0),
(280, 'Simhasanam (2012&#32;film)', '38588ecc3b84abf8d74a1b82e6480837.jpg', '', 1, 'Simhasanam is a 2012 Malayalam action film written and directed by Shaji Kailas, starring Prithviraj, Vandana Menon and Aishwarya Devan in lead roles.[1] The music and background score of the film are composed by Bijibal and Rajamani respectively.', 0),
(281, 'Prakash Bare', 'd343c5d7e3ab6b10d83e656fc70ef082.png', '', 1, 'Prakash bare is a producer and actor in the Indian film industry.[1]', 0),
(282, 'Remya Nambeesan', '788ff9dcc2c2b54eb372d8efb7789fc3.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Remya Nambeesan is an Indian film actress. She made her career debut in 2000 with Sayahnam.[2] Following performances as a child artiste in several Malayalam films during the early 2000s, she went on to play minor supporting roles, before essaying starring roles since 2006. In 2008, she appeared in her first non-Malayalam project, while receiving critical acclaim for her performances in the films Traffic (2011) and Chaappa Kurish (2011). Besides acting, Remya has occasionally worked as a television presenter and singer as well.', 0),
(283, 'P. Balachandran', 'd69adfe51bf1e87c4b72326f576fe6e8.png', '', 1, 'P. Balachandran (born in 2nd February, 1952 at Sasthamkotta ), is one of the most versatile and towering personalities of malayalam literature, cinema and the theatre scene.[1] He is best known for critically acclaimed movies such as Punaradhivasam, Ulladakkam , Pavithram etc. His directorial debut is Ivan Megharoopan. ', 0),
(284, 'Ivan Megharoopan', '0718e02f418cd1d0955f394158455623.jpg', '', 1, 'Ivan Megharoopan (Malayalam: à´‡à´µàµ» à´®àµ‡à´˜à´°àµ‚à´ªàµ») is a 2012 Malayalam biographical film written and directed by P. Balachandran. The film is based on the life of Malayalam poet P. Kunhiraman Nair and is particularly based on his autobiography, Kaviyude Kalpadukal.[1] Prakash Bare, who is the producer of the film, also plays the protagonist K. P. Madhavan Nair.[1]', 1),
(285, 'Akasathinte Niram', 'fb79ef15b50d205ead3499038da6c2bc.png', '', 1, 'Akasathinte Niram (Malayalam: à´†à´•à´¾à´¶à´¤àµà´¤à´¿à´¨àµà´±àµ† à´¨à´¿à´±à´‚; English: Colour of the Sky) is a 2012 Malayalam film directed by Dr. Biju[1] starring Indrajith[2] and Amala Paul[3] in the lead roles.', 1),
(286, 'Ajantha (film)', '30b11f1a1751a4dc8e81b300e0ef2edd.png', '', 1, 'Ajantha is a multilingual film shot in Tamil, Telugu, Kannada and Malayalam. It was directed by Rajppa ravishankar. The Tamil version was released on 30 October 2009[1] and Malayalam version on 19 July 2012.', 1),
(287, 'Mullamottum Munthiricharum', '3f8f27b854284e8e4ef20c403395d3c6.jpg', '', 1, 'Mullamottum Munthiricharum (Malayalam: à´®àµà´²àµà´²à´®àµŠà´Ÿàµà´Ÿàµà´‚ à´®àµà´¨àµà´¤à´¿à´°à´¿à´šàµà´šà´¾à´±àµà´‚) is a 2012 Malayalam film directed by Aneesh Anwar, starring Indrajith, Meghana Raj and Ananya in lead roles.[2] Mohan Sithara is the music director of the film.', 1),
(288, 'Thattathin Marayathu', 'a73ca0e276813540097b9149b9722ce7.jpg', '', 1, 'Thattathin Marayathu is a 2012 Malayalam musical romance film written and directed by Vineeth Sreenivasan, starring Nivin Pauly and Isha Talwar in the lead roles. While the supporting cast includes Aju Varghese, Manoj K. Jayan, Sreenivasan, Sunny Wayne, Bhagath Manuel, Manikuttan, Niveda Thomas along with a list of new debutant actors. The film is produced by Mukesh and Sreenivasan under the banner of Lumiere Film Company. [1][2] The music is composed by Shaan Rahman, while the cinematography is handled by Jomon T. John, and the editing is by Ranjan Abraham. Distribution of the film is done by', 1),
(289, 'Kanika (actress)', 'b797b7cc32f1d565e62c7ec2ffab0de0.jpg', '289a35a33e26652849158831e30343bce62.jpg', 1, 'Divya Venkatasubramaniam (Tamil: à®¤à®¿à®µà¯à®¯à®¾ à®µà¯†à®™à¯à®•à®Ÿà®šà¯à®ªà¯à®°à®®à®£à®¿à®¯à®®à¯; born 3 July 1982[citation needed]), best known by her stage name Kanika (known in Malayalam film industry as Kaniha),[1][2] is an Indian film actress, occasional dubbing artist, playback singer, and TV anchor. Making her debut in the 2002 Tamil film Five Star, she went on to work in other South Indian film industries, including Telugu, Malayalam and Kannada, as well. She is perhaps best known for her performances as Eashwari in her debut film Five Star, Gayathri in Varalaru - History of God', 0),
(290, 'Shankar Ramakrishnan', '024065296f1af527123416e07823afec.png', '', 1, 'Shankar Ramakrishnan is an Indian screen writer and director, who works in Malayalam cinema. He directed a short film, Island Express, for the Malayalam anthology film, Kerala Cafe. He also wrote the script for historical-fantasy film Urumi.[1][2]', 0),
(291, 'Spirit (2012&#32;film)', '10dd944d7ce17e1725cd41714a4e329c.jpg', '', 1, 'Spirit is a 2012 Malayalam satirical film written and directed by Ranjith. The film primarily focuses on the increasing habits of alcoholism in Kerala but is altogether a take on all things contemporary with a satirical tint. It stars Mohanlal, Kaniha and Shankar Ramakrishnan in the lead roles while Lena, Nandu, Thilakan and Madhu play notable supporting roles. The film released on 14 June with positive results.', 1),
(292, 'Menaka (actress)', '031e1b2ba4d7ac10ca13bef60350fdae.jpg', '', 1, 'Menaka is an Indian film actress and producer. She was an native from Nagercoil of Tamil Nadu. In her short film career 1980-86, Menaka acted in 116 films, mostly in Malayalam. She also did a few movies in Tamil, Kannada and Telugu.[1] She has worked with many leading actors of the time, including the late Prem Nazir, Soman and Sukumaran,and opposit to the eighties actors like Shankar,Ratheesh and Nedumudi Venu. She has also acted opposite current superstars Mammootty, Mohanlal, Rajinikanth.', 0),
(293, '22 Female Kottayam', 'd9480fdb2690fead095fbb62f069f6db.jpg', '', 1, '22 Female Kottayam, also known as 22FK, is a 2012 Indian rape and revenge film directed by Aashiq Abu and starring Rima Kallingal and Fahad Fazil in the lead roles.[2] The film deals with the travails of a nurse who was victimised for no fault of hers and who takes revenge on her tormentors in a rather unusual manner. Set and filmed in Bangalore, the film released on April 13, 2012, and received strongly positive reviews from critics. It was also well received at the box-office.[3]', 1),
(294, 'Srikanth (actor)', '15245e4bba0b62e75e11bc42871bb0c9.jpg', '', 1, 'Srikanth (Tamil: à®¸à¯à®°à¯€à®•à®¾à®¨à¯à®¤à¯; born 28 February 1979) is a South Indian film actor who has appeared in Tamil, Telugu and Malayalam language films. He debuted in the 2002 Tamil film Roja Kootam (2002) before going on to make appearances in films such as Parthiban Kanavu (2003), April Maadhathil (2002), Bose (2004), Kana Kandaen (2005), Aadavari Matalaku Ardhalu Verule (2004), Poo (2008), Police Police (2010), Sadhurangam (2011), Nanban (2012), and Nippu (2012).', 0),
(295, 'Yami Gautam', '250d744e83d031abe98b17b7db3195bd.png', '', 1, 'Yami Gautam (born on 24 November 1988) is an Indian film and television actress. Her 2012 film Vicky Donor is her first film in Bollywood. Her earlier appearances are on Indian television serials like Yeh Pyar Na Hoga Kam and Chand Ke Paar Chalo. Her claim to fame role was in Vicky Donor.She is very passionate about her work.', 0),
(296, 'Hero (2012&#32;film)', 'b4c8073895f0ea291450fc9e5faa7269.jpg', '', 1, 'Hero is a 2012 Malayalam action thriller film directed by Diphan of Puthiya Mukham fame.[2] It stars Prithviraj, Srikanth and Bollywood star Yami Gautam in lead roles.[3][4]. The film is produced by Vijayakumar. The soundtrack is scored by Gopi Sunder along with lyrics by Anil Panachooran.', 1),
(297, 'Kaviyoor Ponnamma', '2f1de55a0345a90340e5e6354f640cc1.png?303-4', '2970c7c49c5bcdc7fcd96cb3c2938b1c31b.jpeg', 1, 'Kaviyoor Ponnamma is a Malayalam film actress. She won the Kerala State Award for Best Supporting Actress in 1971,1972,1973,and 1994.', 0),
(298, 'Manjadikuru', '4010290d5f7021ce6e056714fe8007b6.jpg', '', 1, 'Manjadikuru (Malayalam: à´®à´žàµà´šà´¾à´Ÿà´¿à´•àµà´•àµà´°àµ, English: Lucky Red Seeds) is a 2008 Malayalam film written and directed by Anjali Menon. The film was premiered at the 2008 International Film Festival of Kerala, and won the FIPRESCI Award for best Malayalam film and Hassankutty award for Best Debutant Indian director.[1] In 2009, it swept the awards at South Asian International Film Festival (SAIFF) at New York, winning five Grand Jury Awards - Best Film, Best Director, Best Screenplay, Best Cinematographer and Best Emerging Talent. [2][3][4][5]', 1),
(299, 'Diamond Necklace (film)', '9afa6ddfd0aeba3f513a2659dfea1f7a.jpg', '', 1, 'Diamond Necklace is a 2012 Malayalam film directed by Lal Jose, starring Fahadh Faasil, Samvrutha Sunil, Gauthami Nair and Anusree in the lead roles. Released on May 4, 2012 the film received positive reviews from critics. It was a commercial success in metro centers.[2]', 1),
(300, 'Mallu Singh', '8bf50e1ea1d96b9578123eee874c1b3e.jpg', '', 1, 'Mallu Singh (Malayalam: à´®à´²àµà´²àµ‚à´¸à´¿à´‚à´—àµ) is a 2012 Malayalam masala film directed by Vyshakh and written by Sethu. The film stars Unni Mukundan, Kunchacko Boban, Rupa Manjari and Samvrutha Sunil in the main roles, while Biju Menon, Manoj K. Jayan, and Suraj Venjaramood come in other pivotal roles.', 1),
(301, 'Namitha Pramod', 'fa01adb97e8c73f03d00851b756d5f1c.png', '', 1, 'Namitha, is an Indian film actress, who appears in Malayalam films. She made her acting debut in the Malayalam film Traffic. [1]', 0),
(302, 'Nivin Pauly', '40edf7c1acb17dc985797edbe0676ff5.jpg', '', 1, 'Nivin Pauly (born October 11, 1984), is an Indian film actor who predominantly acts in Malayalam films. He is best known for his debut film Malarvadi Arts Club (2010). His second collaboration with Vineeth Sreenivasan, Thattathin Marayathu (2012), created a bigger mark at the box office, as it turned out to be a blockbuster.[1]', 0),
(303, 'Puthiya Theerangal', 'f660038e0bfc96c5ba60f3f30a209fba.jpg', '', 1, 'Puthiya Theerangal (Malayalam:à´ªàµà´¤à´¿à´¯ à´¤àµ€à´°à´™àµà´™à´³àµ) is a 2012 Malayalam film directed by Sathyan Anthikkad, produced by Anto Joseph and written by Benny P. Nayarambalam, starring Nedumudi Venu, Namitha Pramod and Nivin Pauly in the lead roles.[2]', 0),
(304, 'Honey Rose', '0b4ad6815dcf27b69ec8e4ae03909270.jpg', '', 1, 'Honey Rose (also credited as Dhwani or Soundarya) is an Indian film actress, who predominantly acts in Tamil, Malayalam and Telugu films.[1][2]', 0),
(305, 'Trivandrum Lodge', '50310859840736355f8c3d51cdf9b5ff.jpg', '', 1, 'Trivandrum Lodge (2012) is a Malayalam drama film written by Anoop Menon and directed by V. K. Prakash. It stars Jayasurya, Honey Rose and Anoop Menon in the lead roles. The film is produced by P. A. Sebastian under the banner of Time Ads Entertainment and features music composed by M. Jayachandran, whilst cinematography is handled by Pradeep Nair and is edited by Mahesh Narayanan.[1]', 0),
(306, 'Indrajith Sukumaran', '480a096c6bd472085d29fa68b254a025.jpg', '', 1, 'Indrajith Sukumaran (born 17 December 1980)[1] is an Indian film actor best known for his work in Malayalam cinema. He is the son of late actor Sukumaran. Collaborations with director Lal Jose have been appreciated by both audiences and critics alike.', 0),
(307, 'Husbands in Goa', '5c81d734125106943dff36836ec8ffd2.jpg', '', 1, 'Husbands in Goa is a 2012 Malayalam-language comedy film directed by Saji Surendran and written by Krishna Poojapura, starring Jayasurya, Indrajith, Lal, Asif Ali, Rima Kallingal, Bhama, Remya Nambeesan and Praveena.', 0),
(308, 'Ranjith Sankar', '9a1962986ea92cb6c3ddd77ac7c75357.png?303-4', '', 1, 'Ranjith Sankar is an Indian screenwriter and film director, best known for his debut film Passenger (2009).', 0),
(309, 'Molly Aunty Rocks!', 'ed215c7df98243ed16e332c8cabedd91.png', '', 1, 'Molly Aunty Rocks! is a 2012 Malayalam film directed by Ranjith Sankar, starring Revathi in the title role along with Prithviraj. It has been released on 14th September, 2012 to positive reviews from critics and audience alike. The positive energy that is maintained throughout is the highlight of this movie, opined Audience.[1] [2] [3]', 0),
(310, 'Run Babby Run', '686ce562e97c50b6417e49d17e521f59.jpg', '', 1, '[1] Run Babby Run is a 2012 Malayalam comedy-thriller film directed by Joshiy, produced by Milan Jaleel and distributed by Galaxy Films. Written by Sachi of the Sachi-Sethu duo, the film stars Mohanlal and Amala Paul in the lead roles.[2] The cinematography was done by R. D. Rajasekhar and music by Ratheesh Vegha.', 0),
(311, 'Charmy Kaur', '412d502df6fb2f4e37d81196b4a79457.jpg', '', 1, 'Charmy Kaur (also spelt as Charmee or Charmi)[2] is an Indian film actress, who has predominantly appeared in Telugu films. She acted with stars such as Dileep, Nandamuri Balakrishna, Akkineni Nagarjuna, Venkatesh, Jr. NTR, Prabhas, Siddarth, Ravi Teja, Sumanth, Nitin, Silambarasan and mammootty. She is known for her dedication to learn Telugu in short span of time. Charmi gave her voice to Kajal Aggarwal in the film Chandamama (2007).', 0);
