(174, '\nSaguni\n', '', 'The film was first revealed in early April 2011, when it was reported that Karthi was considering a "social satire" script written by debutant film maker, Shankar Dayal, to be his next venture after the success of his previous film Siruthai.[2] Karthi confirmed the news and revealed he would feature in a new get-up for the film, although expressing that the script was still in development.[3][4] Veteran actress Raadhika Sarathkumar signed on to play a supporting role in May 2011[5], whilst Roja signed on to play a doctor in the film and Mumtaj was selected to play a role making her comeback af', '2012-06-22', 0, 2, 1),
